                  "elements": [
                    {
                      "id": "58cbf96",
                      "elType": "widget",
                      "settings": {
                        "title": "Benefits of Vetiver Grass:\n\n",
                        "align": "center",
                        "_margin": {
                          "unit": "px",
                          "top": "29",
                          "right": "29",
                          "bottom": "29",
                          "left": "29",
                          "isLinked": true
                        }
                      },
                      "elements": [],
                      "widgetType": "heading"
                    },
                    {
                      "id": "089ac0a",
                      "elType": "widget",
                      "settings": {
                        "editor": "<p>Vetiver grass offers a range of environmental and economic benefits, including:</p><ul><li><strong>Soil and Water Conservation</strong>: Reduces erosion by up to 90% and enhances water retention.</li><li><strong>Slope Stabilization</strong>: Prevents landslides, protecting infrastructure on steep slopes.</li><li><strong>Disaster Mitigation</strong>: Provides resilience against floods and heavy rainfall.</li><li><strong>Phytoremediation</strong>: Absorbs pollutants like heavy metals, improving soil and water quality.</li><li><strong>Agricultural Improvement</strong>: Boosts crop yields, reduces runoff, and acts as a natural pest barrier.</li><li><strong>Essential Oil Production</strong>: Vetiver oil is valued for its earthy scent and is used in perfumes, skincare, and wellness products.</li><li><strong>Skincare and Cosmetics</strong>: Rich in antioxidants, Vetiver oil helps with anti-aging, moisturizing, and treating acne.</li><li><strong>Aromatherapy</strong>: Promotes relaxation, reduces anxiety, and improves sleep quality.</li><li><strong>Holistic Health</strong>: Supports detoxification, circulation, and emotional well-being.</li><li><strong>Sustainable Handicrafts</strong>: Used in eco-friendly crafts, roofing, and animal fodder, supporting local economies.</li></ul>",
                        "align": "justify",
                        "_margin": {
